1. DEFINITIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

1.1 "Licensor" means Contentrain, LLC, a company organized under the laws
of the Republic of Türkiye, and its affiliates.

1.2 "Licensee" means the individual or legal entity exercising rights
under this License. If the Licensee is an entity, "Licensee" includes
its Affiliates controlled by majority ownership.

1.3 "Contentrain Studio" means the open-source software distributed by
the Licensor under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0
(AGPL-3.0), excluding the Enterprise Edition.

1.4 "Enterprise Edition" or "EE" means all software, source code,
object code, configuration, documentation, and other materials located
in the `ee/` directory of the Contentrain Studio repository, together
with any updates, modifications, or derivative works thereof distributed
by the Licensor.

1.5 "Subscription" means a paid, time-limited entitlement issued by the
Licensor that authorizes use of the Enterprise Edition under a specific
SKU (currently: "Pro", "Enterprise", or any successor SKU designated by
the Licensor in writing). The legacy "Business" SKU is superseded and
has no effect under this License.

1.6 "Managed Service" means the hosted instance of Contentrain Studio
operated by the Licensor at contentrain.io (or any successor domain).

1.7 "Managed Use" means use of the Enterprise Edition solely by
accessing the Managed Service over the public internet, without
receiving, copying, deploying, or executing the EE source code or
binaries outside the Managed Service.

1.8 "On-Premises Deployment" means any installation, execution, or
operation of the Enterprise Edition on infrastructure not controlled
by the Licensor, including Licensee-controlled servers, private cloud,
public cloud accounts owned by the Licensee, or air-gapped environments.

1.9 "Authorized Users" means named individuals (human end users) who
are employees, contractors, or agents of the Licensee and who are
permitted to access the Enterprise Edition, counted per the Subscription
tier. Each distinct human identity counts as one Authorized User,
regardless of how many devices or accounts they use.

1.10 "Production Use" means any use of the Enterprise Edition to
support revenue-generating activity, live customer content, or
business operations. All other use is "Non-Production Use", which
includes development, staging, QA, training, and demonstration.

1.11 "Instance" means a single logical deployment of Contentrain Studio
that includes the Enterprise Edition. A highly-available cluster
serving a single workspace tenant counts as one Instance.

