3. RESTRICTIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

Regardless of license type, the Licensee shall NOT, and shall not
permit any third party to:

3.1 use the Enterprise Edition except as expressly permitted under
    Section 2;

3.2 copy, reproduce, or redistribute the Enterprise Edition source or
    binaries outside the Licensee's own licensed Instances;

3.3 sublicense, sell, rent, lease, or transfer the Enterprise Edition
    or any rights under this License to a third party;

3.4 host, operate, or offer the Enterprise Edition (in whole or in
    part, modified or unmodified, alone or combined with other
    software) as a commercial service to third parties;

3.5 remove, alter, or obscure any copyright, trademark, license, or
    attribution notice in the Enterprise Edition;

3.6 reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Enterprise Edition,
    except to the extent such restriction is prohibited by applicable
    law;

3.7 exceed the Instance, Authorized User, or Production/Non-Production
    scope specified in the applicable order form or Subscription tier;

3.8 use the Enterprise Edition to build, train, benchmark, or improve
    a Competing Product. A "Competing Product" means any product or
    service that (a) substitutes for Contentrain Studio or the Managed
    Service, (b) exposes a substantially similar API surface, or (c)
    offers substantially similar Git-backed structured content
    management functionality to a general audience. Internal use by
    the Licensee for its own non-commercial operations is not a
    Competing Product;

3.9 publish benchmark results, competitive analyses, or performance
    comparisons involving the Enterprise Edition without the Licensor's
    prior written consent;

3.10 use the Enterprise Edition in any manner that violates applicable
     law, including export control and sanctions laws;

3.11 combine the Enterprise Edition with AGPL-3.0 licensed code in a
     manner that would purport to relicense the Enterprise Edition
     under the AGPL-3.0 — the AGPL-3.0 does NOT apply to the Enterprise
     Edition, and any such purported relicensing is void;

3.12 circumvent any technical license enforcement, metering, or
     feature-flag mechanism in the Enterprise Edition.

