4.2 The Enterprise Edition is NOT licensed under the AGPL-3.0. Nothing
in this License or in the AGPL-3.0 shall be interpreted as granting
AGPL-3.0 rights in the Enterprise Edition.

4.3 The Enterprise Edition interacts with the AGPL-3.0 core through
defined interface boundaries (e.g., the `EnterpriseBridge` interface).
This interaction is an "aggregate" as contemplated by AGPL-3.0 §5 and
does not cause the Enterprise Edition to become a covered work under
the AGPL-3.0.

4.4 The Licensor publishes additional terms under AGPL-3.0 §7 for the
core in the `LICENSE-EXCEPTIONS` file, limited to §7(c) attribution
and §7(e) no-trademark terms. These additional terms apply only to
the AGPL-3.0 core and not to the Enterprise Edition. No further
restrictions beyond those expressly permitted by AGPL-3.0 §7(a)–(f)
are imposed on the AGPL-3.0 core.

